{
  "style": "APA",
  "texts": [
    "Employment for individuals with disabilities is an area of policy that has received lengthy considerations, both in terms of supporting disabled people and organisations to create meaningful employment opportunities (Morris, 2018).",
    "In the UK, the Disability Confident Scheme has become a hallmark of employer organizations committed to creating inclusive and accessible workplaces for disabled employees (Department for Work & Pensions, 2014).",
    "At the same time, underwriting employment for many disabled people is the Access to Work scheme, which funds eligible individuals to make necessary adaptations to aid employment (Department for Work & Pensions, 2014).",
    "The first author, Ben, is blind and makes use of screen reading and speech-to-text software, and braille.",
    "Additionally, he requires support to familiarise himself with physical spaces that are not familiar to him, such as a new classroom or workspace."
  ],
  "correct_citations": [
    "Employment for individuals with disabilities is an area of policy that has received lengthy considerations, both in terms of supporting disabled people and organisations to create meaningful employment opportunities (Morris, 2018).",
    "In the UK, the Disability Confident Scheme has become a hallmark of employer organizations committed to creating inclusive and accessible workplaces for disabled employees (Department for Work & Pensions, 2014).",
    "At the same time, underwriting employment for many disabled people is the Access to Work scheme, which funds eligible individuals to make necessary adaptations to aid employment (Department for Work & Pensions, 2014)."
  ]
